modules.description: Provides operations to build and manipulate doubly linked lists, including insertion, deletion, and traversal. Works with nodes containing arbitrary payload data and pointers to previous and next elements. Used to efficiently manage dynamic sequences where frequent modifications at both ends are required.

The module provides operations for converting, manipulating, and inspecting doubly linked lists, including efficient appending, reversing, and element access, alongside list-like transformations such as mapping and folding. It supports parallel element processing across two lists and indexed iteration, enabling precise control over traversal and modification. These capabilities are suited for applications requiring dynamic list management or structured data transformations.
